title: Early wake-up call again for Texas, Oklahoma; Red River Showdown kickoff time announced
text:
Texas and Oklahoma will renew their annual rivalry at the Cotton Bowl in Fair Park at 11 a.m. Oct. 10. ABC will televise the game.
The game time and TV information was announced Monday.
Oklahoma has won four of the last five meetings, including 31-26 in 2014. Texas' last win was a 36-20 victory in 2013, Mack Brown's final season.
